OL,4,CFloods: Research shows millions more at
OL,5,Crisk of flooding
OL,6, A new study shows that the percentage
OL,7, of the global population at risk from
OL,8, flooding has risen by almost a quarter
OL,9, since the year 2000.
OL,11,FSatellite images were used to document
OL,12,Fthe rise, which is far greater than had
OL,13,Fbeen predicted by computer models.
OL,15,FThe analysis shows that migration and a
OL,16,Fgrowing number of flood events are
OL,17,Fbehind the rapid increase.
OL,19,FBy 2030, millions more will experience
OL,20,Fincreased flooding due to climate and
OL,21,Fdemographic change, the authors say.
